5:
...Very well, we shall have the
humans and the fiends live just
beyond the Silver Woods, but on
opposite sides. Does that sound
acceptable?
16:
Could I just confirm one more time...
Are you certain we should have the
beastmen live apart from the fiends?
17:
Your people and theirs have
established rapport in a
considerably short amount of time—
21:
That is why they must be separated.
Collusion breeds rebellion.
24:
They bond over a shared bitterness
toward humanity... Bonds forged
only from hatred will never last.
30:
P-pardon the intrusion, but there is
a situation which requires your
attention—
37:
Remnants of the Lord of Shadow's
army are instigating an uprising.
Daemons have been spotted in a
village to the north!
40:
...It appears that we needn't have
worried about the beastmen.
44:
Do you need assistance? The
warriors of the Silver Woods can be
mobilized at a moment's notice.
48:
Not for a matter of this degree. 
I will handle this myself.
56:
Allow me to send at least an
escort—to observe and report back
to me. Is that an agreeable enough
pretense?
60:
...It is a reasonable precaution. 
Do what you must.
64:
...2 stronger units, and less than 10
regular soldiers. As far as uprisings
go, this is pathetic.
67:
Alk. Nimbus. We hit them hard and
fast.
75:
Aren't we only supposed to be
scouting? That's why we left the rest
of your troops behind... and I got
glared at super hard when we left...
81:
If we brought them over, they'd
simply wipe out the entire village.
86:
Wipe... out?! But how could they do
that to their own people?
90:
Their shared blood only serves as an
offense to their pride.
93:
It is one of the reasons why they
chose to defy their Lord and join
with me instead.
98:
So in other words, bad blood's still
bad blood even when it's shared.
101:
For 50 years, the Lord of Shadow
bolstered the ranks of daemons,
weakening the army's strength in
the process...
103:
To my soldiers, the daemons are
sullied beings, as well as the source
of years of resentment.
106:
There might be a curse wielder
among them. If pushed into a
corner...
115:
But it won't come to that if we finish
this quick and clean.
117: And I know we can pull it off if we try.
122:
Full disclaimer though. If things go
south, it's a free for all.
137:
This is our chance, take them
now!
Cursebringer!
141:
I take it you are the curse wielder
here.
145:
Surrender. Daemons are no longer
able to regenerate. You have no
hope of victory left.
148:
Lord Oghir, the time has come for
me to join you...
154:
O ever-encompassing darkness,
grant me one last wish! Take my
flesh as sacrifice—
164:
But if you yet feel hope in your heart
for a better tomorrow...
173:
Curses are but one power the dead
leave behind. There are other things
they can entrust to the living.
179:
Your power may yet be useful. Join
me, if you wish.
181:
Or continue to drown in your curse
and die. It is your choice.
190:
...I see. You quelled the rebellion
yourself.
193:
Exactly as stated in the written
report.
196:
If I may broach another subject...
Have you heard the news? There's
been an influx of fiends joining the
residential area.
200:
I have heard. So the doors are open
to all refugees.
204: They are indeed. I made sure of it.
207:
...That's all from me. Thank you for
your report.
210:
I trust the escorts I assigned were
satisfactory, Adjudicus?
216:
You chose your allies well, Lilith
Stratos.
221:
I don't believe it. Was that a smile on
his face?
